abstract: With President Donald Trump's impeachment trial looming in January, the five Democratic senators running against him are weighing tele-townhalls, quick trips and candidate proxies to keep their White House bids going while they serve as jurors.
snippet: With President Donald Trump's impeachment trial looming in January, the five Democratic senators running against him are weighing tele-townhalls, quick trips and candidate proxies to keep their White House bids going while they serve as jurors.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With President Donald Trump's impeachment trial looming in January, the five Democratic senators running against him are weighing tele-townhalls, quick trips and candidate proxies to keep their White House bids going while they serve as jurors.
headline_main: January Juggle: Senators in 2020 White House Race to Balance Impeachment, Campaigning
headline_print_headline: January Juggle: Senators in 2020 White House Race to Balance Impeachment, Campaigning

abstract: President Donald Trump's campaign has embraced Democratic-led efforts to impeach him as a major asset to his 2020 re-election campaign, betting that his supporters and disaffected political independents will be motivated to vote for him next November.
snippet: President Donald Trump's campaign has embraced Democratic-led efforts to impeach him as a major asset to his 2020 re-election campaign, betting that his supporters and disaffected political independents will be motivated to vote for him next Novem...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - President Donald Trump's campaign has embraced Democratic-led efforts to impeach him as a major asset to his 2020 re-election campaign, betting that his supporters and disaffected political independents will be motivated to vote for him next November.
headline_main: Trump Campaign Says Impeachment Backfiring. Not Really, Polls Suggest
headline_print_headline: Trump Campaign Says Impeachment Backfiring. Not Really, Polls Suggest

abstract: Republican Donald Trump is this week likely to become the third U.S. president to be impeached when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
snippet: Republican Donald Trump is this week likely to become the third U.S. president to be impeached when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican Donald Trump is this week likely to become the third U.S. president to be impeached when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
headline_main: Trump on Track to Become Third U.S. President to Be Impeached
headline_print_headline: Trump on Track to Become Third U.S. President to Be Impeached

abstract: The mayor of Alabama’s largest city is endorsing Joe Biden for the 2020 Democratic Party presidential nomination just weeks after the vice president met with a group of Southern black mayors representing millions of voters in key early primary states.

abstract: Safa al-Sarray was killed when Iraqi forces fired a tear-gas canister at his head.
snippet: Safa al-Sarray was killed when Iraqi forces fired a tear-gas canister at his head.
lead_paragraph: Iraqis have been protesting since early October against the dysfunctional and corrupt political system installed by the United States after the 2003 occupation. Unlike previous waves of protests that began in 2011, this protest was spontaneous and not organized by any party.

headline_main: I Will Visit Your Grave When I Go to Iraq

abstract: The rule of law is the principle that protects every American from the abuse of monarchs, despots and tyrants.
snippet: The rule of law is the principle that protects every American from the abuse of monarchs, despots and tyrants.
lead_paragraph: The privilege of being the only American in our history to serve as the director of both the F.B.I. and the C.I.A. gives me a unique perspective and a responsibility to speak out about a dire threat to the rule of law in the country I love. Order protects liberty, and liberty protects order. Today, the integrity of the institutions that protect our civil order is, tragically, under assault from too many people whose job it should be to protect them.

abstract: It’s a huge undertaking to slow climate change, but we’ve done big things before.
snippet: It’s a huge undertaking to slow climate change, but we’ve done big things before.
lead_paragraph: Decades of climate change foot-dragging are finally giving way to public demands for action. Around the world, millions of young people are on the march. Political and business leaders are making pledges and offering plans.

abstract: It’s about much more than amassing money or people.
snippet: It’s about much more than amassing money or people.
lead_paragraph: From Hong Kong to Chile to the United States, people around the world are angry. They don’t have a say in things that matter in their lives. So they protest, sign petitions, call their lawmakers and organize sit-ins. Despite this enormous energy, their actions can often feel futile. How can we make them add up to something more, so people have power over the things they care about?

abstract: Two months after Spain's biggest soccer match was postponed due to political unrest, Barcelona host Real Madrid on Wednesday in a La Liga fixture that could have a huge impact on the title race and will take place amid fresh protests.
snippet: Two months after Spain's biggest soccer match was postponed due to political unrest, Barcelona host Real Madrid on Wednesday in a La Liga fixture that could have a huge impact on the title race and will take place amid fresh protests.
lead_paragraph: BARCELONA — Two months after Spain's biggest soccer match was postponed due to political unrest, Barcelona host Real Madrid on Wednesday in a La Liga fixture that could have a huge impact on the title race and will take place amid fresh protests.
